findings.code_snippet:
cleanup: async () => {
  await client.close()
  await server.close()
}

findings.suggestion:
Wrap cleanup in try/finally to guarantee both close calls execute:

cleanup: async () => {
  try { await client.close() } finally { await server.close() }
}

Consider a small helper:

function parseJsonResponse(content: Array<{type: string, text: string}>, label: string) {
  const text = content[0]?.text ?? ''
  try { return JSON.parse(text) }
  catch { throw new Error(`${label} returned invalid JSON: ${text.slice(0, 200)}`) }
}
